OL,3,CLaurence Fox denies encouraging people
OL,4,Cto damage Ulez cameras
OL,6,FEncouraging someone to threaten damage
OL,7,Fto property can result in the same
OL,8,Fsentence as making the threat, which
OL,9,Fis up to 10 years in prison, the
OL,10,FSentencing Council confirmed. Fox was
OL,11,Fgranted unconditional bail to attend
OL,12,FCroydon Crown Court on 13 June.
OL,14,FCameras have been repeatedly damaged
OL,15,Fafter the Ulez area was expanded to
OL,16,Fcover all of London in 2023.They allow
OL,17,FTransport for London (TfL) to monitor
OL,18,Fthe cars that enter and exit the zone.
